-- Zodiac Plans Acquisitions in New Business Areas, Zarrouati Tells Figaro
-- B y   M a t t h e w   C a m p b e l l
-- 2010-09-21T05:34:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-21/zodiac-plans-acquisitions-in-new-business-areas-zarrouati-tells-figaro.html
Zodiac Aerospace  plans acquisitions
to build its presence in cabin equipment and in new business
areas, Le Figaro reported, citing an interview with Chief
Executive Officer  Olivier Zarrouati .  Some of the company’s defense assets are not “at the heart
of our business” as a supplier of civilian equipment, Zarrouati
said, adding that defense businesses account for 6 to 7 percent
of revenue, the newspaper cited Zarrouati as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Matthew Campbell  in Paris via 
 mcampbell39@bloomberg.net . 